subject: Swimming
lead_paragraph: The opening night at the Australian swimming championships and Olympic trials in Sydney produced two world records. Stephanie Rice broke the world mark in the 400-meter individual medley, finishing in 4 minutes 31.46 seconds. Emily Seebohm broke the world record in the non-Olympic 50-meter backstroke. Seebohm finished in 27.95 seconds.
